vans and Gracia's conversations, as one or the other tells what he finds meaningful in a given work. Sparkling with insight, their exchanges allow the reader to eavesdrop on two celebrated intellectuals-worldly, erudite, and unafraid to disagree-as they reflect on the pleasures of seeing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh1 aAdál, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerrano, Andres, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarza, Carmen Lomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade la Torre, Einar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOller, Francisco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGracia, Jorge J. E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 ade la Torre, Jamex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasquiat, Jean-Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBedia, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzaceta, Luis Cruz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYampolsky, Mariana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamírez, Martín, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampos-Pons, María Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrito, María, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822376880zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822376880423Coveruhttps://www.degru